radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild stranding about the pancreas, tiny subcentimeter hypodensities within the liver likely biliary hamartomas, no intra- or extra-hepatic bile duct dilation, gallbladder, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, and intra-abdominal loops of small and large bowel are normal, mild colonic diverticulosis without evidence of diverticulitis, no acute fracture.
